Pay quartiles 

CDC employed 512 people as at 31 March 2017 which means there are 128 
employees per pay quartile.  The gender split per quartile is detailed below.  

The hourly rates that represent each quartile are as follows: 

  Lower - relates to the hourly rates up to £11.57 
  Lower middle - relates to the hourly rates of £11.57 - £13.80   
  Upper middle - relates to the hourly rates of £13.80 – £17.56 
  Upper - relates to the hourly rates of £17.56 and above 

 

  

